/root partition should be bigger, the following is too small:
/dev/mapper/gargle--vg-root  9.1G  6.5G  2.2G  76% /

make it 16G



see https://www.choam.eu/altgr-intl/ or http://users.telenet.be/gargle/debian/ on how to configure altgr-weur

gargle@msi:~/eeepc$ cat /etc/default/keyboard 
# KEYBOARD CONFIGURATION FILE

# Consult the keyboard(5) manual page.

XKBMODEL="pc105"
XKBLAYOUT="us"
XKBVARIANT="altgr-weur"
XKBOPTIONS="compose:lwin,ctrl:nocaps"

BACKSPACE="guess"

run setupcon as root to update the console keyboard. Make sure /etc/default/keyboard has a new timestemp or setupcon won't do anything.



ducky one 2 sf customisation
Left-WINDOWS arrow-down 5 seconds to reset keyboard
FN ALT K 5 seconds FN Left-WINDOWS ESC to switch FN and Left-WINDOWS key
FN ALT 2 to switch to customisation 2
FN ALT TAB 5 seconds ESC FN ESC FN ALT FN ALT TAB 1 second to make ESC do ` and ~
FN ALT TAB 5 seconds FN ESC ESC FN ALT FN ALT TAB 1 second to make FN ESC do ESC



gargle@msi:~/eeepc$ cat /etc/default/locale 
#  File generated by update-locale
LANG="en_GB.UTF-8"
LANGUAGE="en_GB:en"

# BEWARE, the alt key doesn't work in xterm with UTF-8 unless we add
# xterm*metaSendsEscape: true in .Xresources

# instead of modifying /etc/sudoers
/usr/sbin/usermod -a -G sudo gargle
/usr/sbin/usermod -a -G sudo betton



As root, set uxterm as x-terminal-emulator:
update-alternatives --config x-terminal-emulator



Change the following lines in /etc/X11/app-defaults/XTerm-color:
! Uncomment this for black text on a "white" background.
*VT100*foreground: black
!*VT100*background: gray90
*VT100*background: white



vi /etc/X11/app-defaults/UXTerm
! Making the wide fonts associated with *VT100.font in this file allows uxterm
! to skip that step.  It will use the fonts that the XTerm file gives for the
! *VT100.uft8Fonts.font pattern.
*VT100.font2:	-misc-fixed-medium-r-normal--8-80-75-75-c-50-iso10646-1
!*VT100.font: -misc-fixed-medium-r-semicondensed--13-120-75-75-c-60-iso10646-1   <<< comment original
*VT100.font:	-misc-fixed-medium-r-normal--14-130-75-75-c-70-iso10646-1        <<< and copy from font3
*VT100.font3:	-misc-fixed-medium-r-normal--14-130-75-75-c-70-iso10646-1
*VT100.font4:	-misc-fixed-medium-r-normal--13-120-75-75-c-80-iso10646-1
*VT100.font5:	-misc-fixed-medium-r-normal--18-120-100-100-c-90-iso10646-1
*VT100.font6:	-misc-fixed-medium-r-normal--20-200-75-75-c-100-iso10646-1
*VT100.font7:	-adobe-courier-medium-r-normal--24-240-75-75-m-150-iso10646-1

! Here is an alternate set of fonts with better support for bold:
!*VT100.font2:	-efont-biwidth-medium-r-normal--10-100-75-75-p-50-iso10646-1
!*VT100.font:	-efont-biwidth-medium-r-normal--10-100-75-75-p-50-iso10646-1
!*VT100.font3:	-efont-biwidth-medium-r-normal--12-120-75-75-p-60-iso10646-1
!*VT100.font4:	-efont-biwidth-medium-r-normal--14-140-75-75-p-70-iso10646-1
!*VT100.font5:	-efont-biwidth-medium-r-normal--16-160-75-75-p-80-iso10646-1
!*VT100.font6:	-efont-biwidth-medium-r-normal--24-240-75-75-p-120-iso10646-1

vi ~/.Xresources
XTerm*renderFont: true
XTerm*faceName: DejaVu Sans Mono
XTerm*faceSize: 10

UXTerm*renderFont: true
UXTerm*faceName: DejaVu Sans Mono
UXTerm*faceSize: 10

xterm*metaSendsEscape: true


xrdb -merge ~/.Xresources
xrdb -q

and set the default font in emacs:
 '(default ((t (:family "DejaVu Sans Mono" :foundry "PfEd" :slant normal :weight normal :height 98 :width normal)))))



